title: Grateful Dead Live at Zoo Amphitheater on 1981-07-05
lineage: Dat (Sony R500) -> Samplitude Professional v11.1 -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street-> Promised Land, Candyman-> Cassidy, Brown Eyed Women-> CC Rider, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Althea-> Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Don't Ease Me In-> The Music Never Stopped, Ship of Fools-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: First Show My first Show. Didn't know many songs of theirs when I got there but it changed my life.  Hard for me to compare the show to anything else. Shakedown opened the show and I still think it's a great version.  C. C. Rider is splendid here too. I remember people dancing with the trees and the trees dancing with the people during Mexicali. Before the show, on July 5, it was so hot and no clouds in the sky, but one. That little Cloud drifted right over the audience and rained and cooled everybody down. Everybody was looking at each other wanting to ask if it really happened, but no one did. I still don't know if it really happened. My girlfriend at the time had huge hooters and was not wearing a bra. The looks she got were priceless. I became a Dead Head that day.

Very Cool Groove! This show has that and then some! Catch the "Hard to Handle" groove in the 'Shakedown' jam. Lesh is all over it. 

Thank you, Charlie Miller!

Gold plated Lost Sailor>SoC>He's Gone but I can't agree on the Shakedown -- Jerry doesn't sound like he knows where he is. But once he settles in it's a very good show, first and second sets are equally strong.
shakedown human induced seismic tremors here folks!

First Set Jerry is tearing it up! Jerry is totally in the present, and playing with intension!
As such, this soundboard (with Jerry vocal dropouts in Shakedown, unfortunately) is killer. The first set grabbed my attention, but its all good...perhaps second set is just not as stunningly so!
This being an edit for this Actual version... appears the vocal issues on the soundboard I downloaded back a few years ago, aren't actually on this version! I have to go check my records about which SBD version I have in my playlist... and listening still further, I was quite incorrect... not vocal dropouts, lead guitar, what the hell did I think I heard... It was just a dream I dream long ago?
well balanced SBD band is on Yet another great SBD via Charlie Miller mahalo!

Notable for.... ....for the early second set Don't ease and MNS.  Its like they kept wanting to play first set slot songs.  Otherwise, a fine show.

On a side note, I love Psiclone's review down on the bottom, those anecdotal posts are my favorite.

Hot!! The person that wrote the review at bottom is right.  I was there and it poured rain for about 5 min, unbelievable!! Then it was back to sunshine and very hot 102F and excellent music. My first Dead show, went with my older bro and his friends. Sat right in front of the tapers. Bought a t-shirt that I still have today 2022.
